The '''University of Health Sciences Antigua''' ('''UHSA''') is a [[private university|private]], [[For-profit school|for-profit]] [[medical school]] located in Dowhill near [[Falmouth, Antigua and Barbuda|Falmouth]], [[Antigua]], in the [[Caribbean]]. UHSA confers upon its graduates the [[Doctor of Medicine]] (MD) degree.<ref name='a'>https://imed.faimer.org/details.asp?country=130&school=&currpage=1&cname=ANTIGUA+AND+BARBUDA&city=&region=CA&rname=Central+America%2FCaribbean&mcode=130010&psize=25</ref>

==History==
UHSA was established in 1982 and began instruction in 1983.<ref name='a' /> The Dowhill campus is located about {{convert|12|mi|km}} from the capital city of [[St. John's, Antigua and Barbuda|St. John's]]. Formerly a [[NASA]] tracking station, the university is located on an {{convert|50|acre|m2|adj=on}} area within the Historical National Park area of [[English Harbour]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Bat's Cave, Antigua|url=http://travel.aol.com/travel-guide/mexico-and-caribbean/antigua-and-barbuda/antigua/bat-s-cave-thingstodo-detail-227014/|accessdate=17 August 2011}}</ref>

==Curriculum==
The Doctor of Medicine program at UHSA is a four year course of study that consists of three semesters per calendar year. Semesters 1–4 are [[Medicine#Basic_sciences|basic sciences]] semesters that are completed at the university's Antigua campus. The remainder of the program consists of [[clerkship (medicine)|clinical clerkships]] at affiliated hospitals in the United States, [[Puerto Rico]], the United Kingdom, and China.<ref>{{cite web|title=UHSA Affiliated Hospitals|url=http://www.uhsa.ag/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=237&Itemid=259|publisher=UHSA School of Medicine|accessdate=18 August 2012}}</ref>

UHSA also offers an MD program for current health professionals. For semesters 1-5, students spend the first four weeks of each semester in Antigua, and complete the remainder of the curriculum via online distance learning.<ref>{{cite web|title=MD for Health Professionals|url=http://www.uhsa.ag/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=569&Itemid=160|publisher=UHSA|accessdate=18 August 2012}}</ref>

==Accreditation==
UHSA is recognised by the Government of Antigua and Barbuda.<ref>{{cite web | last = Government of Antigua and Barbuda | title = Antigua and Barbuda Government Directory | url = http://www.ab.gov.ag/gov_v1/resident/education.htm | accessdate =5 September 2006 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070927212331/http://www.ab.gov.ag/gov_v1/resident/education.htm |archivedate = 27 September 2007}}</ref> The university is listed in the [[FAIMER]] [[International Medical Education Directory]] (IMED)<ref name='a' /> and in the [[Avicenna Directories#AVICENNA Directory for medicine|AVICENNA Directory for medicine]].<ref>http://avicennadb.ku.dk/avicenna/viewSchool.php?school=M00017&type</ref>

==Licensure restrictions==
